{{Short description|Government gazette of Japan}} [[File:Japan official Gazette logo.png|thumb|right|130px|The logo of the Kanpō, the Japanese [[:en:Government gazette|Government gazette]]]] [[File:SeifuKankoubutsuSC.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The former Government Publications Service Center at [[:en:Kasumigaseki|Kasumigaseki]], Tokyo]] '''Kanpō''' ({{Langx|ja|官報}}, literally "Official report") is the [[:en:Government gazette|official gazette]] of the [[:en:Japanese government|Japanese government]]. <ref>{{cite web |title=Official Gazette Overview |url=https://www.npb.go.jp/en/books/kanpo.html |website=National Printing Bureau |access-date=March 31, 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230505130546/https://www.npb.go.jp/en/books/kanpo.html |archive-date=May 5, 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Jones |first1=Colin |title=The Kanpo: Where everything in Japan goes to happen (officially) |url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/community/2018/08/05/issues/kanpo-everything-japan-goes-happen-officially/#.XmAo06hKjb0 |access-date=March 31, 2024 |work=The Japan Times |date=August 5, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240303160717/https://www.japantimes.co.jp/community/2018/08/05/issues/kanpo-everything-japan-goes-happen-officially/#.XmAo06hKjb0 |archive-date=March 3, 2024}}</ref> Its official publication started in 1886, from the [[:en:National Printing Bureau|National Printing Bureau]] of the [[:en:Ministry of the Treasury|Ministry of Finance]].
Japanese people historically relied on the ''[[:en:Kōsatsu|Kōsatsu]]'', a wooden plaque placed at [[shukuba]] and other important places, to learn of proclamations made by either the [[:en:Shogun|Shogun]] or the local [[daimyo]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://wiki.samurai-archives.com/index.php?title=Kosatsu |title=Kosatsu (SamuraiWiki) |access-date=2020-03-04 |archive-date=2015-09-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150909230302/http://wiki.samurai-archives.com/index.php?title=Kosatsu |url-status=dead }}</ref> As the [[:en:literacy rate|literacy rate]] improved and the modern nation emerged under the [[:en:Government of Meiji Japan|Government of Meiji Japan]], the kōsatsu was abolished in 1873 and eventually replaced by the ''Kanpō'', the Japanese [[:en:Government gazette|Government gazette]], which is now available on the [[:en:Internet|Internet]].
==See also== *[[:en:Public notice|Public notice]] *[[:en:Kōsatsu|Kōsatsu]]
